caption: I work around the corner and have eaten here 8-10 times probably. The food is always very delicious and fresh, and it’s usually around $12 for lunch. Everyone who works there is always nice and professional and one time they gave me a free cookie just for buying lunch on a Saturday.
BEST SALADS HANDS DOWN. FRESH EVERYTIME. I literally order every Friday, soo good!
Love the food but do NOT believe their hours.  They are never open until 7pm on ANY day.  They close at 3pm so this is a place I can never eat at again.
Great tasty easy salad place
The food was super appetizing.
Service is always nice even when they have a full house. The service was very kind and attentive. Prices that won't shock you.
Service is always excellent even when they have a full house. If it wasn't far from my work I would come by more.
got there about three, it wasn't crowded. the staff was very kind and attentive. it has a good feel to it. kinda of like a restaurant in los angeles i loved to visit.
one of the best spots in the area. definitely worth a return trip.
Awesome salad!

Website says they’re open until 7:30. Wanted to be safe, so I called at 6:28 to verify how late they were open. Woman said 7. Arrived at 6:32 to everything all packed up. The two women working didn’t even say anything to me. They just looked at each other and shrugged. Trying to support local businesses but not ones that are rude and don’t want business. Do not recommend.

I can't wait till they open more of these places in the suburbs. Seems like they only have them in the city for now. This place was so good! Everything was super fresh and tasty and delicious. All they serve is salads you can choose from the options they already have or you can create your own.  I got me the Harvest Bowl which is organic wild rice, shredded kale, apples, sweet potatoes, roasted chicken, local goat cheese, toasted almonds, balsamic vinaigrette. It tasted so good just typing this review makes me want to drive to the city to get me another one.  Every time I'm around the city I'm for sure stopping here.
Awesomeness
We had it delivered, fast, fresh and a good amount of food for the price - we had a sandwich, flatbread and two salads for under $45 with delivery, it will be one of our go-to’s going forward!
Service is fast. Salads are delicious.
Tony the best  Best salads in Chicago
Hands down my favorite salad place in Chicago. They don't rip you off with toppings like other salad places and everything is always very fresh and high quality. MG Guacamole Greens is my go to!!

Have been coming here for a couple years now and the food has always been fantastic. Just yesterday I decided to order online so I could avoid the lines during lunch time.  I screwed up and ended up ordering from the other location on Franklin. When I arrived to pick up my food they couldn't find it (because I didn't order from the right location). No questions asked they made me a new salad and I was out of there in under 5 minutes. Thank you again for fixing MY mistake and not making me deal with it myself.  Top notch service as always!
Can’t go wrong with green salad! Nice service good stuff!

Amazing salads with fresh ingredients! A bit expensive but that's to be expected in the middle of a city. It's worth it. Modern seating. Can be hard to get seating at lunch time. There is indoor and outdoor seating.
Everyone at our table was quite pleased. Definitely worth a return trip.

Enjoying the Mexicali salad. Price is about right, I wish salads didn’t cost so much! Anyway, I love the strong cilantro flavor and the two dressings, one being peanut-based, make a delicious combination. Better than sweet greens IMO.
Awesome salads
(Translated by Google) Delicious taste  (Original) Delicioso sabor
I don't buy lunch at work unless it's this place. The salads are delicious.
For when you want/need roughage but don't feel like gathering all the many ingredients, prepping then mixing! This place has so many fresh choices.
Cubano panini is an excellent choice!
Great salad
Great food as always!!
Love this place.
I love this place for lunch. No nonsense delicious food. The salads are fantastic, pizzas yummy. Healthy quick spot that won't disappoint.
Something no one will tell you - they have some of the best cookies in the city.
Delicious fresh salads and soups, this is a must for healthy eaters.

Mixed Greens is THE spot to eat in River North! Healthy options that taste fantastic and don't break your wallet. They catered UFC Gym River North's member appreciation party and did a great job as well. Quality/friendly ownership, management, and staff. Check them out - and try the turkey panini if you're not going with a salad!
(Translated by Google) Super delicious pizzas  (Original) Pizzas super deliciosas
Big fresh salads good sandwiches
Mediocre to the nth degree.  Overpriced for what you get. It's as if they are trained to give you as little as possible.
The salads in this place are delicious!!
Great place and prices. The food is amazing and they are fast.
Love it
I love the steakhouse salad! This is a nice fast healthy option!
Ingredients are always fresh and I love that they chop the salad and mix it.
Great salads and dressings.

So I got the create your own salad, and at the end I asked for crispy chicken, however they accidentally gave me grilled chicken. I really did not like the grilled chicken, at all. I called and they exchanged my salad, for the remade salad for me with the right chicken. I got it on the side just in case. So delicious! And the BEST double chocolate chip cookie I've ever had. I will definitely come back to try a panini.  Update: You wouldn't think to try a Cuban panini at a mostly salad place, but am I glad I did. Amazing.
Fantastic options. Their paninis are incredible.
Their costumer service is excellent and there is a wide verity if choices
Good price for good salads and soups!

Interesting little spot in the basement if a nondescript building in River North. It was empty when I came here, but that was due to it being a Saturday after a heavy snow. The soup was solid and they have a lot of options. My wife and I split the grilled cheese with sun dried tomatoes, which paired well with the soup. The other menu items looked tasty as well.
I'm not a big salad fan, but I'm a fan of Mixed Greens' salads. Consider ordering online to avoid the huge weekday lunch lines, though.
Good food (salads and sandwiches).
Best salad I ever had! Will post pics soon
The MG Guacamole salad is amazing!!

Hi there If you are looking for a place to eat some delicious and healthy, this is for you. We can find diferent healthy salads, paninis, pizzas and more, all with good prices. The staff is friendly and the service is quickly. You really would be to try.
Great spot for a custom or predetermined salads.  I have heard the flatbread and pizzas are great as well.
I don't see what the big deal is for salad, it's just lettuce and vegetables. Sandwiches here are good though.
A lot of options, well-priced, super fast and great service.  Great place to bring clients at lunchtime, even if the lines get a little long.
Fast yummy salads

It is the best place for salad. There is a good variety of ingredients to build your own.  During the weekend there no wait. The pizza is also good. It is nice to sit outside during the summer, even if the metro is very close and makes it noisy.
Nice choices
I love the make your own unlimited with honey poppyseed dressing!!!
Like their salads
Pretty decent salads and sandwiches quick for lunch
Top notch salad options with high quality ingredients.
They have good options for you to choose from.  They move through the lunch crowd fairly quickly.

Grateful to have a place almost directly across the street from work where I can run in a grab a salad. They have several salads you can just name and they make the fresh while you wait, for a very short period of time. Or you can create your salad from the generous amount of ingredients they have on display. I particularly like the black and blue salad and my old standby the cob salad . They will either put the dressing on, or put it on the side. When I asked for it on the salad, it was the perfect amount. The salads are never dripping and gooey from the dressing, just enough the make the salad delicious. They also serve paninis and pizzas, though i have not tried those as of yet.
Parking is not too great but the food is.
Quick, quality salads. Even if there is a line out of the door it moves fast. One of the best options for lunch in an area that has a severe lack of lunch offerings. Prices are reasonable.
Totally messed up order. Blamed it on postates. Dont order from here
Consistently fresh salad ingredients. Salads are perfect.
Salad every day.
Good for salads and sandwiches.  Lines are long so, be prepared to wait.  Order online and to save time.
Nice salad choices
One of the better salad places in Chicago
Amazing salads. Healthy and tasty, nothing more could be asked for. This is the kind of place where you feel about yourself after eating.
Great salads!
10$ for a very good mixed salad.
Great for a light lunch. You can build your own salad.
Crowded at lunch time because there's nothing else comparable in the area
Great lunch spot. Build your own salad. If there is a line don't worry it goes quick

I haven't tried there salads but they look pretty tasty. I ordered a panini. I waiting for close to 40 minutes. The person I was with had already finished their salad. I didn't really want to wait any longer so I left. Maybe I will try again someday.
Good, fresh ingredients. Large variety.

I don't know much about the rest of their menu, but this place consistently makes THE BEST salads out of any restaurant my company orders from on Seamless.  Every single ingredient is on point, every time.  I could not ask for a better lunch.

Really liked coming here to get my salads! First time coming in it seemed really confusing and their menu is not in the best spot. Staff is super friendly I just wish there was more options. Overall like coming to this place in the summer time!

I used to work right by Mixed Greens and would eat it for lunch pretty much everyday! It is so delicious and fast. They have tons of options so I never got bored with eating it a lot. I highly recommend for a quick, healthy lunch.
Like this place a lot! Always great service. Cashiers should smile more.
This place is great, cheap and quick.

Very fresh ingredients. This place always has a line out the door exactly @ noon, so you know that they are moving product. If you go around 12:45 - 1:15 you get the most fresh ingredients and no line. It' really is a good fresh option for food in the loop.
I come here basically all the time. Try to honey-lime dressing; you won't regret it.
